import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data = data.groupby(['symbol']).mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['symbol'], data['price'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c', '#d62728', '#9467bd'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Company')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Stock Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the average stock price for each company?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    for company in data['symbol'].unique():
        company_data = data[data['symbol'] == company]
        ax.plot(company_data['date'], company_data['price'], label=company)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of stock prices over time for each company?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['day'] = data['date'].dt.day
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', hue='symbol', multiple='stack', ax=ax, kde=True, palette='bright')
    ax.set_xlabel('Stock Price')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of stock prices for each company?')
    ax.legend(title='Company', loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.pivot(index='date', columns='symbol', values='price')
    corr = data.corr()
    sns.scatterplot(x=corr['AAPL'], y=corr['IBM'], hue=corr.index, legend=False)
    plt.axhline(y=0.5, color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between stock prices of different companies?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Correlation between AAPL and IBM')
    plt.ylabel('Correlation between GOOG and IBM')
    plt.legend(loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1.0, 0.5))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
